The article is a message from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, regarding a supplemental consolidated report on the global deployments of U.S. Armed Forces equipped for combat. The report covers ongoing U.S. contingency operations overseas, including combat operations in Afghanistan against al-Qa'ida terrorists and their Taliban supporters, as well as deployments in various locations in support of overseas operations. The President states that additional measures will be taken, as necessary, to protect U.S. citizens and interests, which may include short-notice deployments of special operations and other forces. The U.S. Armed Forces, with international partners, continue to pursue al-Qa'ida terrorists and eliminate support to al-Qa'ida, as well as engage remaining al-Qa'ida and Taliban fighters in Afghanistan. The President also mentions the U.S. contribution of forces in Iraq, efforts to enhance counterterrorism capabilities globally, maritime interception operations to stop the movement of international terrorists, and contributions to peacekeeping efforts in Kosovo. The President concludes by stating that he has directed the participation of U.S. Armed Forces in these operations based on his constitutional authority.